5:
And that's that—I'm more or less
done.
8: R-really?! Wasn't that way too fast?
12:
Are you sure this is wise? You're a
marked man—going alone could be
dangerous.
15:
In times like these, working solo is
the best—allows you to be quick on
your feet.
17:
That and... this is something I must
do. I'm well aware of the dangers
involved.
29:
It hasn't even been a week since you
left!
33:
I made sure to put many things in
motion beforehand.
39:
Having those connections with the
Swes family was certainly a huge
help.
42:
If we're going to have talks with the
Farlands, I'd prefer everything be
done properly—and with the right
people.
44:
What's more is, it seems the internal
strife in the Swes house had
something to do with this matter as
well.
47:
In the end, what we really need right
now is friends.
52:
Well... At least you managed to nip it
in the bud, right?
58:
Are you going to report this to your
sister?
62:
Yes, about that. I'm afraid I've been a
terrible brother.
64: I must find a way to make amends.
73:
The pancakes here are to die for. Or,
if you're feeling adventurous, they've
got all sorts of other wild dishes.
What do you say?
75:
I'm afraid I can stomach neither
sweet nor spicy food. I will have to
pass.
76:
...I would like to once again extend
my gratitude for this meeting,
Brother.
78:
You're most welcome.
My congratulations on successfully
stealing that Guild Council seat.
81:
But thwarting Father's foolish plots is
something you could have done
yourself, no?
83:
What you really wanted was the
connections I have at my
disposal—the Sweses and Dul
Kugala.
86:
Regardless, it seems you've
managed to make a positive
impression on them, so I have
nothing to worry about.
89:
I knew you were sharp, Brother, 
but I must admit... 
I am nonetheless taken aback.
91:
I suppose if I had a bone to pick... 
It would be that you weren't more
honest with me earlier.
93:
If you were a gentler man, I might
have done so.
97:
This makes it clear enough then—we
are both siblings and rivals.
100:
That combination will make us
wonderful collaborators, don't you
think?
102:
Is that to say you have a request of
me? Depending on the content, 
I could perhaps oblige.
105:
There's a man looking at us from the
second floor window of a house
right behind me.
108:
He'll probably follow you as well. This
type of nuisance will only get in our
way—I'd like you to help me do
something about him.
110: Do I really have a say in the matter?
112:
It's likely you'll get stuck dealing with
his kind sooner or later. Best to get
used to it now.
114:
He's part of a group of people
smuggling all sorts of curious
artifacts from Palpebra. Some are
likely headed to Tiatha.
116:
I want to follow him and see the
route he takes. Will you assist me?
119: I see. In that case, yes. I will.
121:
One more thing—have you ever
heard of the Star Augurs?
123:
The name sounds familiar... Is the
man following us one of them?
125:
No, I doubt it. They're probably a few
layers deeper. This isn't the only
place they operate, after all...
128:
Still, it's plainly clear that they are
our enemies. You'd do well to
remember their name.
132:
Congratulations again on your new
position, Elena.
Till we meet again.
137:
I won't lose to you, you know. I'll be a
fierce rival.
148:
Ah, sorry—I got a little excited there. 
I don't usually shoot first and ask
questions later, but I'm just in such a
fine mood today.
150: Well, anything to say for yourself?
153:
Gah... I... I saw everything! We know
who you are, Quade Arsalett!
155:
Now we know how to get to you...
That girl... is your weakness!
158: My... weakness? You can't be serious.
160: She's my rival and kindred spirit.
164: And I won't stand to lose to her.
